Uses of Package
model

Packages that use model
Package
Description
controller
The controller package contains all the classes responsible for managing the interactions between the user, the model and the view of the Tic-Tac-Toe game.
model
The model package contains the classes that define the logic and state of the Tic-Tac-Toe game (in progress, invalid move, win, tie).
view
The view package contains all the classes related to the display of the graphical user interface of the Tic-Tac-Toe game.
  • Classes in model used by controller
    Class
    Description
    GameState
    This enum represents the possible states of a Tic-Tac-Toe game: a win for one of the players, a tie, a game in progress, and an invalid move.
    TicTacToeBoard
    This class represents a Tic-Tac-Toe board and implements the Board interface.

    Description

    TicTacToeBoard.Tile
    Inner class representing a tile on the Tic-Tac-Toe board.
    UserPlayer
